verses.text_plain: O Lord my God, in thee do I put my trust: save me from all them that persecute me, and deliver me:
verses.verse_html:
1O Lord my God, in thee do I put my trust: save me from all them that persecute me, and deliver me: ▼
▼ words: or, business

tokens.text: in thee do I put my trust
me from all them that persecute

verses.text_plain: Lest he tear my soul like a lion, rending it in pieces, while there is none to deliver.
verses.verse_html:
2Lest he tear my soul like a lion, rending it in pieces, while there is none to deliver. ▼
▼ none…: Heb. not a deliverer

footnotes.body_html: ▼ none…: Heb. not a deliverer

verses.text_plain: O Lord my God, if I have done this; if there be iniquity in my hands;
verses.verse_html: 3O Lord my God, if I have done this; if there be iniquity in my hands;

verses.text_plain: If I have rewarded evil unto him that was at peace with me; (yea, I have delivered him that without cause is mine enemy:)
verses.verse_html: 4If I have rewarded evil unto him that was at peace with me; (yea, I have delivered him that without cause is mine enemy:)

tokens.text: unto him that was at peace

verses.text_plain: Let the enemy persecute my soul, and take it; yea, let him tread down my life upon the earth, and lay mine honour in the dust. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 5Let the enemy persecute my soul, and take it; yea, let him tread down my life upon the earth, and lay mine honour in the dust. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Arise, O Lord, in thine anger, lift up thyself because of the rage of mine enemies: and awake for me to the judgment that thou hast commanded.
verses.verse_html: 6Arise, O Lord, in thine anger, lift up thyself because of the rage of mine enemies: and awake for me to the judgment that thou hast commanded.

verses.text_plain: So shall the congregation of the people compass thee about: for their sakes therefore return thou on high.
verses.verse_html: 7So shall the congregation of the people compass thee about: for their sakes therefore return thou on high.

verses.text_plain: The Lord shall judge the people: judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to mine integrity that is in me.
verses.verse_html: 8The Lord shall judge the people: judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to mine integrity that is in me.

verses.text_plain: Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end; but establish the just: for the righteous God trieth the hearts and reins.
verses.verse_html: 9Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end; but establish the just: for the righteous God trieth the hearts and reins.

verses.text_plain: My defence is of God, which saveth the upright in heart.
verses.verse_html:
10My defence is of God, which saveth the upright in heart. ▼
▼ My…: Heb. My buckler is upon God

footnotes.body_text: ▼ My…: Heb. My buckler is upon God
footnotes.body_html: ▼ My…: Heb. My buckler is upon God

verses.text_plain: God judgeth the righteous, and God is angry with the wicked every day.
verses.verse_html:
11God judgeth the righteous, and God is angry with the wicked every day. ▼
▼ judgeth…: or, is a righteous judge

footnotes.body_text: ▼ judgeth…: or, is a righteous judge
footnotes.body_html: ▼ judgeth…: or, is a righteous judge

verses.text_plain: If he turn not, he will whet his sword; he hath bent his bow, and made it ready.
verses.verse_html: 12If he turn not, he will whet his sword; he hath bent his bow, and made it ready.

verses.text_plain: He hath also prepared for him the instruments of death; he ordaineth his arrows against the persecutors.
verses.verse_html: 13He hath also prepared for him the instruments of death; he ordaineth his arrows against the persecutors.

verses.text_plain: Behold, he travaileth with iniquity, and hath conceived mischief, and brought forth falsehood.
verses.verse_html: 14Behold, he travaileth with iniquity, and hath conceived mischief, and brought forth falsehood.

verses.text_plain: He made a pit, and digged it, and is fallen into the ditch which he made.
verses.verse_html:
15He made a pit, and digged it, and is fallen into the ditch which he made. ▼
▼ He made a pit: Heb. He hath digged a pit

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He made a pit: Heb. He hath digged a pit
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He made a pit: Heb. He hath digged a pit

verses.text_plain: His mischief shall return upon his own head, and his violent dealing shall come down upon his own pate.
verses.verse_html: 16His mischief shall return upon his own head, and his violent dealing shall come down upon his own pate.

verses.text_plain: I will praise the Lord according to his righteousness: and will sing praise to the name of the Lord most high.
verses.verse_html: 17I will praise the Lord according to his righteousness: and will sing praise to the name of the Lord most high.
